statement.p:
Consider the function f:\Z \to \Z given by f(n) = \begin{cases}n+1 \amp  \text{ if }n\text{ is even} \\ n-3 \amp \text{ if }n\text{ is odd} . \end{cases}






    Is f injective? Prove your answer.






    Is f surjective? Prove your answer.
